sk.upjs.gursky.bplustree
Interface BPObject<K,O>

Type Parameters:
K - The class of the BPKey implementation
O - The class of the BPObject implementation
All Superinterfaces:
Comparable<O>, Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
BPObjectIntDouble
public interface BPObject<K,O>
extends Comparable<O>, Serializable

In BPTree entries are organized and sorted by key values in inner nodes and by BPObjects in leafs. Key values are parts of BPObjects. Two BPObjects MUST be comparable first by key value and than by other values in BPObjects. Every BPObject must be able to serialize itself to the ByteBuffer. Every BPObject in the tree must have equal maximal size, i.e. the method getSize() must return a constant equal value for BPObjects in a tree.

getSize

int getSize()
Method returns the maximal number of bytes needed to store a BPObject to a ByteBuffer. Method must return a constant (final static) value for all instances. For example, if the key is of type int, and the other value in BPObject is double this method should always return 12 (4+8). If the size of the BPObjects differs between instances, this value stands for the maximal size.

Returns:
size needed to store this type of BPObject.
